Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day. You are eligible for an audiology screen.  Please follow up with reception to help book your slot.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.

------------------------------
Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Comment Value: None

Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.

------------------------------
Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Nil
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day. You are eligible for an audiology screen.  Please follow up with reception to help book your slot.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

------------------------------
Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day. You are eligible for an audiology screen.  Please follow up with reception to help book your slot.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day. You are eligible for an audiology screen.  Please follow up with reception to help book your slot.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.

------------------------------
Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.

Men's Health Recommendations:

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.
Comment Key: LifestyleRecommendation
Comment Value: None

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.

Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.

Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: -Continue health & cancer screening as advised. Pay attention to the conditions that have occurred in your family.

------------------------------
Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Comment Key: MensHealthRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.
Comment Key: MensHealthRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations:

Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.

------------------------------
Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Comment Value: None

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Overview Notes: Slightly increased cholesterol: try to manage with lifestyle alone. Eat a healthy diet, continue exercising, decrease your weekend alcohol consumption and manage your stress. Supplement with 2g per day of omega 3.
Comment Key: ReportNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day. You are eligible for an audiology screen.  Please follow up with reception to help book your slot.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.
Comment Key: SpecialInvestigationNote
Comment Value: Nil
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: 0
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningRecommendation

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Repeat your mammogram yearly and your pap smear every 1 - 2 years.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.

Employee: Samantha Forbes
Report Date: 2020-12-01
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day. You are eligible for an audiology screen.  Please follow up with reception to help book your slot.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Menopausal changes can be difficult to navigate. Please speak to your doctor to find ways to help you through this period.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level: supplement with vitamin D and recheck in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level between 50 to 80 ng/ml. Vitamin D is not only important for your bones but also your mood and cognitive health. It is also has anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties.
